# Upwork Job Workspace Execution Rule

When the user pastes a new job post in chat, create a dedicated job folder and write all deliverables as separate markdown files.

## Trigger

Run this workflow whenever the user provides a new job description or job post text.

## Folder Location

Create the job folder in the workspace root unless the user requests a different location.

## Folder Naming Rule (Mandatory)

Use this pattern:

`001-job-title-slug`

Rules:
- Start at `001` for the first job folder.
- Increment by 1 for each new job (`002`, `003`, ...).
- Convert title to lowercase slug with hyphens.
- Remove special characters.
- Keep the title short but identifiable.

Example:
`001-shopify-subscription-box-redesign`

## Required Files (Mandatory)

Create these files in each new job folder:

1) `01-job-post.md`
- Paste or summarize the original job post clearly.

2) `02-business-ideas.md`
- Generate ideas using the Business Idea Rule style and structure.
- Keep recommendations personalized to that exact job.

3) `03-business-flowchart.md`
- Generate flowchart output using the Business Flowchart Rule style and structure.

4) `04-loom-video-script.md`
- Generate 3 script versions using the Loom Video Script Rule style and structure.

5) `05-proposal.md`
- Generate proposal using the Upwork Proposal Writing Rule style and structure.

## Output Quality Rules

- Keep language simple, human, and direct.
- Avoid generic text and copy-paste tone.
- Personalize all files to the exact job context.
- Ask short clarification questions first when critical details are missing.

## Consistency Rules

- Keep all files in markdown format (`.md`).
- Do not merge multiple deliverables into one file.
- Use a clear title at the top of each file.
- Follow each specialized rule for content style and layout.

## If User Shares Multiple Jobs

- Create one folder per job post.
- Continue numbering in sequence.
- Keep each job's files isolated in its own folder.
